# Ransomware Behaviour Detection
## Overview
Detection rule developed to identify early-stage ransomware
encryption activity across enterprise endpoints.
## Threat
Ransomware actors encrypt files by renaming them with
specific extensions or performing high-volume file
rename operations in short timeframes.
## Detection Logic (YARA-L pseudocode)
- Trigger: >100 file rename events within 60 seconds
- AND file extension matches known ransomware patterns
 (.encrypted, .locked, .crypto etc.)
- AND process is NOT whitelisted backup software
## MITRE ATT&CK
- Technique: T1486 - Data Encrypted for Impact
- Tactic: Impact
## Outcome
Rule deployed in Google Chronicle. Tuned threshold
to reduce false positives from legitimate backup
software mass-rename operations.
